    People also ask
    Which season crop is sesame?
    kharif
    The productivity of sesame is low in India, because the crop is mainly grown in kharif.

    Sesame - ICAR-Indian Institute Of Oilseeds Research

    What are the post harvest techniques in sesame?
    The sesame seeds are roasted before crushing. Heating is done to remove excess water from the seeds after the cleaning process. Seeds with less than 9 % moisturecontent (added with palm jaggery in case of cold pressed oil) arepressed by screw press or hydraulic press at less than 70°C temperature.

    Sesame Processing - TNAU Agritech Portal :: Post Harvest Technology

    tnau.ac.in
    https://agritech.tnau.ac.in › postharvest › pht_oilseeds
    tnau.ac.in

    What is the maturity of sesame seed?
    Physiological maturity (PM) normally occurs 95-110 days after planting. PM is when 75% of the capsules on the main stem have mature seed. The plant is very leafy, but will self-defoliate at maturity. Sesame normally dries down in 120-150 days.

    How is sesame oil harvested?
    Sesame oil is obtained by pressing the roasted oilseeds and consumed as a naturally flavored oil without refining. Sesame oil is also extracted without roasting using pressing, sold as virgin oil. The refined version of the oil is also used for salad dressing.
